A pressure leak in a containment buildinghatch at FPL Group Inc's Turkey Point nuclear plant has forceda brief reactor shutdown, a Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC)spokesman said.    Ken Clark, the NRC's representative in Atlanta, said noradioactivity escaped during the incident last night, which hedescribed as "a relatively minor problem that poses no safetyhazard."    Clark said repairs were underway and Turkey Point Unit 4,one of two nuclear reactors at the site south of Miami, wasexpected to be reactivated later today. Reuter&#3;